NAME: CPUVR_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: CPU_VR_PGOOD Is a signal present when CPU_VR_EN is presenT. CPU_VR_PGOOD is a prerequisite along with ALL_SYS_PWRGD to create PM_S0_PGOOD and PM_PCH_PWROK and PM_PCH_SYS_PWROK which are necessary for the machine to turn on and boot.

NAME: ADAPTER_EN
DESCRIPTION: SMC_ADAPTER_EN enables the machine to work off of the power adapter when the proper power adapter is attached. Attacching an 85w Macbook Pro 15” power adapter to a 13” Macbook that requires a 60w power adapter is ok, attaching a 45w Macbook Air power adapter to a 15” macbook Pro that needs an 85w power adapter will result in SMC_ADAPTER_EN missing.

NAME: SMBUS_SMC_BSA_SCL
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_SMC_BSA_SCL is another way to say SMBUS_SMC_5_G3_SCL, look at the definition provided for SMBUS_SMC_5_G3_SCL as it applies to

NAME: PPVIN_S0SW_LCDBKLT
DESCRIPTION: PPVIN_S0SW_LCDBKLT is PPBUS_G3H backlight voltage entering the backlight boost circuit once the transistor has been told to allow it through.

NAME: SSD_PWR_EN
DESCRIPTION: SSD_PWR_EN is a signal that tells the chip making the power rail for the SSD to turn on when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: P3V3S3_EN
DESCRIPTION: P3V3S3_EN is a signal that turns on the PP3V3_S3 power rail when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: PP1V8_SUS
DESCRIPTION: PP1V8_SUS is a 1.8v power rail active in a suspend state.

NAME: PPVTTDDR_S3
DESCRIPTION: PPVTTDDR_S3 is a 3.3v power rail that powers the DDR RAM when the machine is in an S3 suspend to RAM state.

NAME: SMBUS_BATT_SCL
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_BATT_SCL is the clock line of an I2C data line between the battery charging chip that creates PPBUS_G3H, the system management controller(SMC), the battery, and the battery indicator LED.

NAME: CHGR_CSO_N
DESCRIPTION: CHGR_CSO_N is one of the current sense lines for the battery. Resistance between CHGR_CSO_N and CHGR_CSO_P should be the resistance should be the total series resistance of the current sense resistors in the circuit, usually about 2.2 ohms

NAME: BUTTON_DISABLE
DESCRIPTION: BUTTON_DISABLE disables the trackpad when SMC_LID is below 0.5v and the system believes the lid is closed.

NAME: SMBUS_CHGR_SDA
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_CHGR_SDA is the data line of an I2C data line between the battery charging chip that creates PPBUS_G3H, the system management controller(SMC), the battery, and the battery indicator LED.

NAME: LVDS_IG_BKL_ON
DESCRIPTION: LVDS_IG_BKL_ON is equivalent to LCD_BKLT_EN. This signal usually goes to an LED driver used for creating a power rail for the LCD screen backlight, to tell it to turn on & create this rail.

NAME: PPVBAT_G3H_CHGR_R
DESCRIPTION: This is a power rail between the battery and a current sense resistor before the battery power feeds current to the rest of the machine.

NAME: LVDS_DDC_CLK
DESCRIPTION: LVDS_DDC_CLK Is the DDC clock line between the graphics processor and the screen. DDC is a protocol for identifying a screen so that you know what resolution/refresh rate it wants. This is necessary for screen detection, inductor on this data line must be good and DDC voltage must be going to the LCD screen for it to work.

NAME: PPBUS_3GH
DESCRIPTION: PPBUS_3GH is a typo of PPBUS_G3H. If you see someone type PPBUS_3GH assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: SMC_TCK
DESCRIPTION: SMC_TCK is a signal that must be pulled up to 3.42v in order for the SMC to be in the proper mode to function. Often this is not pulled up because of corrosion or corroded resistors by the SMC.

NAME: I2C_BKLT_SDA
DESCRIPTION: I2C_BKLT_SDA is a data line between the LCD screen and the LED driver. This data line cannot short to ground. If it does, the screen cannot talk to the LED driver, and the LED driver will not allow the circuit to produce a backlight.

NAME: BKLT_SDA
DESCRIPTION: BKLT_SDA is a data line between the LCD screen and the LED driver. This data line cannot short to ground. If it does, the screen cannot talk to the LED driver, and the LED driver will not allow the circuit to produce a backlight.

NAME: P3V42_G3H
DESCRIPTION: P3V42_G3H is a typo of PP3V42_G3H

NAME: PPVIN_S5_HS_GPU_ISNS
DESCRIPTION: PPVIN_S5_HS_GPU_ISNS is PPBUS_G3H after going through a current sense resistor to components that create power rails for the GPU.

NAME: CHGR_CSO_P
DESCRIPTION: CHGR_CSO_P is one of the current sense lines for the battery. Resistance between CHGR_CSO_P and CHGR_CSO_N should be the resistance should be the total series resistance of the current sense resistors in the circuit, usually about 2.2 ohms

NAME: PP1V5_S3RS0
DESCRIPTION: PP1V5_S3RS0 is a 1.5v power rail present when the machine is in an S3 suspend to RAM state

NAME: CPUIMVP_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: CPUIMVP_PGOOD is a signal from the CPU VCORE buck converter IC that indicates CPU power is good which is necessary to create PM_S0_PGOOD.

NAME: KERNEL_TASK
DESCRIPTION: KERNEL_TASK is a process that will take up all the CPU and cause the macbook to run very slow when there is a sensor issue. When you see KERNEL_TASK as a process taking up lots of CPU and the machine is working very slow or has loud fans, use a program like hwmonitor to check voltage, amperage, and temperature sensors and look for something that doesn’t look right.

NAME: P5VS3_EN_L
DESCRIPTION: P5VS3_EN_L is a signal that enables the PP5V_S3 power rail when it is low.  _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v.

NAME: HALL_SENSOR_LEFT
DESCRIPTION: HALL_SENSOR_LEFT is a signal from the hall sensor on the left side of the machine that indicates that the lid has been closed. This is necessary for setting SMC_LID properly so the machine knows whether it is closed or open. When this is low, the machine will think it is closed which may cause it to go to sleep or have no backlight on the screen

NAME: SMC_LRESET_L
DESCRIPTION: SMC_LRESET_L is a typo of SMC_RESET_L.

NAME: CHGR_CSI_N
DESCRIPTION: CHGR_CSI_N is one of the current sense lines for the charger. Resistance between CHGR_CSI_N and CHGR_CSI_P should be the resistance should be the total series resistance of the current sense resistors in the circuit, usually about 20.02 ohms

NAME: SMC_TDI
DESCRIPTION: SMC_TDI is a signal that must be pulled up to 3.42v in order for the SMC to be in the proper mode to function. Often this is not pulled up because of corrosion or corroded resistors by the SMC.

NAME: SMC_TPAD_RST_L
DESCRIPTION: SMC_TPAD_RST_L is a signal that comes from the trackpad that can reset the SMC when it is low.  _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v. The trackpad having corrosion from liquid damage is a very common cause of no light on the magsafe charger & the system not turning on, when the trackpad or trackpad cable is corroded and holding this line down.

NAME: PP3V_G3H_RTC
DESCRIPTION: PP3V_G3H_RTC is a 3v power rail present when the machine is in a G3H mechanical off state that powers the RTC circuit.

NAME: PPVCORE_S0_GFX_REG
DESCRIPTION: PPVCORE_S0_GFX_REG is a power rail that powers the GPU in an S0 working state.

NAME: VCC_MAIN
DESCRIPTION: VCC_MAIN is the main power rail in an iPhone that comes from the battery, similar to PPBUS_G3H in a macbook.

NAME: PPVOUT_S0_KBDBKLT
DESCRIPTION: PPVOUT_S0_KBDBKLT is a power rail that powers the LED light in the keyboard backlight. When this is low or missing, the keyboard will not light up.

NAME: PP1V35_CAM
DESCRIPTION: PP1V35_CAM is a 1.35v power rail to power the webcam.

NAME: CPUVR_PGOOD_R
DESCRIPTION: CPUVR_PGOOD_R is a signal that comes from CPU_VR_EN that is necessary along with ALL_SYS_PWRGD to create PM_S0_PGOOD

NAME: SMC_TMS
DESCRIPTION: SMC_TMS is a signal that must be pulled up to 3.42v in order for the SMC to be in the proper mode to function. Often this is not pulled up because of corrosion or corroded resistors by the SMC.

NAME: PP5V_SO
DESCRIPTION: PP5V_SO is a typo of PP5V_S0, which is a 5v power rail present when the machine is in an S0 working state. The person who typed PP5V_SO thought that the S0 in PP5V_S0 was SO, if you see PP5V_SO assume the user made a typo and meant to type PP5V_S0

NAME: SSD_RESET_CONN_L
DESCRIPTION: SSD_RESET_CONN_L is a signal that goes to the SSD that will put it in RESET mode which will keep it from working, when SSD_RESET_L is present. _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v.

NAME: PP0V9_SSD
DESCRIPTION: PP0V9_SSD is a power rail that powers the soldered on NAND memory for the SSD on Macbooks with soldered on storage and must be present for the SSD to show up.

NAME: SMC_MANUAL_RST_L
DESCRIPTION: SMC_MANUAL_RST_L resets the SMC when low.   _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v.

NAME: LCDBKLT_BOOST
DESCRIPTION: LCDBKLT_BOOST is connected to the SWITCH(SW) pin of the LED driver and is switched to ground quickly after the inductor in the DC to DC boost circuit that boosts PPBUS_G3H to backlight voltage for the screen.

NAME: CHGR_CSI_P
DESCRIPTION: CHGR_CSI_P is one of the current sense lines for the charger. Resistance between CHGR_CSI_P and CHGR_CSI_N should be the resistance should be the total series resistance of the current sense resistors in the circuit, usually about 20.02 ohms

NAME: SMBUS_CHGR_SCL
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_CHGR_SCL is the clock line of an I2C data line between the battery charging chip that creates PPBUS_G3H, the system management controller(SMC), the battery, and the battery indicator LED.

NAME: SMC_TDO
DESCRIPTION: SMC_TDO is a signal that must be pulled up to 3.42v in order for the SMC to be in the proper mode to function. Often this is not pulled up because of corrosion or corroded resistors by the SMC.

NAME: SMBUS_BATT_SDA
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_BATT_SDA is the data line of an I2C data line between the battery charging chip that creates PPBUS_G3H, the system management controller(SMC), the battery, and the battery indicator LED.

NAME: HALL_SENSOR_RIGHT
DESCRIPTION: HALL_SENSOR_RIGHT is a signal from the hall sensor on the RIGHT side of the machine that indicates that the lid has been closed. This is necessary for setting SMC_LID properly so the machine knows whether it is closed or open. When this is low, the machine will think it is closed which may cause it to go to sleep or have no backlight on the screen

NAME: AP_RESET_L
DESCRIPTION: AP_RESET_L resets the wifi hardware when it is low, which will keep it from working. AP_RESET_L needs to be high for reset to not be asserted.  _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v.

NAME: 3V3_S0SW_LCD
DESCRIPTION: 3V3_S0SW_LCD is a 3.3v power rail present when the system is in an S0 working state that powers the LCD screen image circuitry. This is necessary to get an image on the screen

NAME: LVDS_DDC_DATA
DESCRIPTION: LVDS_DDC_DATA Is the DDC data line between the graphics processor and the screen. DDC is a protocol for identifying a screen so that you know what resolution/refresh rate it wants. This is necessary for screen detection, inductor on this data line must be good and DDC voltage must be going to the LCD screen for it to work.

NAME: PPVRTC_G3_OUT
DESCRIPTION: PPVRTC_G3_OUT is a 3.3v power line that comes out of the clock chip.

NAME: P3V3S5_EN_R
DESCRIPTION: P3V3S5_EN_R is an enable signal that turns on the PP3V3_S5 power rail.  Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high. The _R means the signal is asserted when the voltage is high(3.3v).

NAME: P5VS4RS3_EN_R
DESCRIPTION: P5VS4RS3_EN_R is an enable signal that turns on the PP5V_S4RS3 power rail. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high. The _R means the signal is asserted when the voltage is high(3.3v).

NAME: PM_BATLOW
DESCRIPTION: PM_BATLOW is a signal that tells the system the battery is too low for it to turn on & keeps it from turning on

NAME: USBC_XA_CC2
DESCRIPTION: USBC_XA_CC2 is a line between the USB-C muxing chip such as the CD3217 or CD3215 and the USB-C charger. Communication must happen on this line in order for the USB-C charger to put out 20v.

NAME: PPVCORE_CPU
DESCRIPTION: PPVCORE_CPU is an abbreviation of PPVCORE_S0_CPU. When you see someone type PPVCORE_CPU, assume they meant to type PPVCORE_S0_CPU.

NAME: LCDBKLT_EN_DIV
DESCRIPTION: LCDBKLT_EN_DIV must be low in order for the P channel MOSFET to have a lower voltage on the gate than is present on the source to allow backlight voltage to flow through the backlight circuit.

NAME: CHGR_CELL
DESCRIPTION: CHGR_CELL is a signal going to the ISL6258, ISL6259, ISL9239, or ISL9240 battery charging chip that sets PPBUS_G3H voltage. Macbook Airs with 2 cells in series  in their batteries will have PPBUS_G3H voltages of 8.15v to 8.55v, Macbooks & Macbook Pros with 3 cells in series in their batteries will have PPBUS_G3H voltages of 12.23 to 12.56v.

NAME: PBUS_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPBUS_G3H When you see PBUS_G3H, assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: P5V_S3
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP5V_S3 When you see P5V_S3, assume they meant to type PP5V_S3

NAME: BLK_EN
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of BKL_EN When you see BLK_EN, assume they meant to type BKL_EN

NAME: SMBUS_SMC_0_S0_SCL
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_SMC_0_S0_SCL is a clock line on the data line between the system management controller(SMC), temperature sensors, GPU, and ALS(ambient light sensor). If this line is pulled down the machine may run slow or have the fans run fast all the time because the SMC can’t tell what the temperature of parts of the machine like fin stack are. Usual problem is bad webcam, unplug webcam to see if it fixes problem.

NAME: PPBUS_G3
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPBUS_G3H. When you see PPBUS_G3, assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: PP5V_S0_ALSCAM_F
DESCRIPTION: PP5V_S0_ALSCAM is a power rail for the webcam and the ambient light sensor.

NAME: PPVOUT_LCDBKLT
DESCRIPTION: PPVOUT_LCDBKLT is the backlight power rail that is responsible for creating a backlight o nthe screen.

NAME: BATLOW_L
DESCRIPTION: This signal tells the system that the battery is low, when the signal is low. Anytime you see an “_L” after a signal, that means that the signal is present when it is a low voltage, typically 0 volts to 0.5 volts

NAME: PP5V_S0_LCD
DESCRIPTION: PP5V_S0_LCD is 5 volts going to the LCD when the machine is in an S0 working state to power the image circuitry of the LCD. When this is missing it is usually because 1) The screen is not detected or is the wrong screen 2) the GPU is not working 3) The inductor between the LCD connector & the 5v rail is blown due to someone plugging the cable in wrong 4) the chip creating it is dead

NAME: SPI_MLB_MOSI
DESCRIPTION: SPI_MLB_MOSI is a line between the SPI ROM BIOS chip and resistors that sit between it and the PCH. This often corrodes on Macbook Airs due to liquid damage and results in missing PM_SLP_S4_L and no bootup.

NAME: DDRREG_EN
DESCRIPTION: DDRREG_EN is an enable signal that turns on power rails for DDR memory

NAME: PLT_RST
DESCRIPTION: PLT_RST stands for platform reset.

NAME: WS_KBD_ONOFF_L
DESCRIPTION: WS_KBD_ONOFF_L is a signal that comes from the keyboard that tells the SMC that the power button has been pressed.  L means whatever before the L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v. This signal directly affects SMC_ONOFF_L

NAME: PP2V7_NAND
DESCRIPTION: PP2V7_NAND is a power rail that powers the soldered on NAND memory for the SSD on Macbooks with soldered on storage and must be present for the SSD to show up.

NAME: USBC_XB_CC1
DESCRIPTION: USBC_XB_CC1 is a line between the USB-C muxing chip such as the CD3217 or CD3215 and the USB-C charger. Communication must happen on this line in order for the USB-C charger to put out 20v.

NAME: PM_SLP_S4L
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PM_SLP_S4_L When you see PM_SLP_S4L, assume they meant to type PM_SLP_S4_L

NAME: ALL_SYS_GOOD
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ALL_SYS_PWRGD When you see ALL_SYS_GOOD, assume they meant to type ALL_SYS_PWRGD

NAME: PP3V3_SO
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_SO is a typo of PP3V3_S0

NAME: BLK_PWM
DESCRIPTION: BLK_PWM is a typo of BKL_PWM. When you see BLK_PWM assume the poster meant to type BKL_PWM. BKL_PWM sets the brightness of the screen. The system will send a PWM signal to BKL_PWM pin to set brightness. If this is low, backlight voltage will boost higher than PPBUS_G3H input, but not enough to make the screen light properly.

NAME: SMBUS_SMC_0_S0_SDA
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_SMC_0_S0_SDA is a data line between the system management controller(SMC), temperature sensors, GPU, and ALS(ambient light sensor). If this line is pulled down the machine may run slow or have the fans run fast all the time because the SMC can’t tell what the temperature of parts of the machine like fin stack are. Usual problem is bad webcam, unplug webcam to see if it fixes problem.

NAME: PLT_RESET
DESCRIPTION: PLT_RESET stands for platform reset. When this is asserted the machine will not POST.

NAME: PP3V3S3_EN
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3S3_EN is a typo of P3V3S3_EN, which is a signal that turns on the PP3V3_S3 power rail when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: SMC_WIFI_PWR_EN
DESCRIPTION: SMC_WIFI_PWR_EN is a signal that turns on power to the wifi circuit when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: USBC_XB_CC2
DESCRIPTION: USBC_XB_CC2 is a line between the USB-C muxing chip such as the CD3217 or CD3215 and the USB-C charger. Communication must happen on this line in order for the USB-C charger to put out 20v.

NAME: P3V3G3S_EN
DESCRIPTION: P3VG3S_EN is a signal that turns on the PP3V3_G3S power rail. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: PPVIN_S5_H5_COMPUTING_ISNS
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPVIN_S5_HS_COMPUTING_ISNS When you see PPVIN_S5_H5_COMPUTING_ISNS, assume they meant to type PPVIN_S5_HS_COMPUTING_ISNS

NAME: SMC_PM_G2
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_PM_G2_EN When you see SMC_PM_G2, assume they meant to type SMC_PM_G2_EN

NAME: P5VS3_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: P5VS3_PGOOD indicates that the PP5V_S3 power rail is functioning properly.

NAME: SMC_LID_R
DESCRIPTION: SMC_LID_R is the signal coming from the hall sensor that detects whether the laptop screen is closed or open. This must be high in order for SMC_LID to be high. SMC_LID has to be high for the machine to not fall asleep and for it to have a backlight.

NAME: ALL_SYS_PWGD
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ALL_SYS_PWRGD. When you see ALL_SYS_PWGD, assume they meant to type ALL_SYS_PWRGD

NAME: I2C_BKLT
DESCRIPTION: I2C_BKLT is a data line between the LCD screen and the LED driver. This data line cannot short to ground. If it does, the screen cannot talk to the LED driver, and the LED driver will not allow the circuit to produce a backlight.

NAME: P5VS5_EN
DESCRIPTION: P5VS5_EN is a signal that turns on the PP5V_S5 power rail. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: LCDBKLT_FB
DESCRIPTION: LCDBKLT_FB is a feedback line between backlight output and the feedback pin on the LED driver. When this connection is broken, backlight output will be equal to PPBUS_G3H voltage of the system rather than boosting. Since this point is the highest voltage in the system, it is the fastest to corrode when liquid damaged, so it is a very common point to check when there is no backlight.

NAME: PP2V5_NAND
DESCRIPTION: PP2V5_NAND is a power rail that powers the NAND memory for the soldered on SSD of newer macbooks and must be present for the internal SSD to work.

NAME: PP3V3_G3S_EN
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_G3S_EN is a signal that enables the PP3V3_G3S power rail when present. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: PP1V8_CAM
DESCRIPTION: PP1V8_CAM is a 1.8v power rail for powering the webcam

NAME: SMC_BCACOK
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_BC_ACOK When you see SMC_BCACOK, assume they meant to type SMC_BC_ACOK

NAME: SPI_MLBROM_CS_L
DESCRIPTION: SPI_MLBROM_CS_L is a signal that goes between the SPI ROM chip and another chip on machines with quad SPI, that can frequently corrode on 13” Macbook Air from 2015 because it is near the corner where liquid seeps in. This being corroded can stop PM_SLP_S4_L from being present.

NAME: USBC_TB_CC2
DESCRIPTION: USBC_TB_CC2 is a line between the USB-C muxing chip such as the CD3217 or CD3215 and the USB-C charger. Communication must happen on this line in order for the USB-C charger to put out 20v.

NAME: PP5V5_S5
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP5V_S5 When you see PP5V_S5, assume they meant to type PP5V_S5

NAME: PP1V8_S4
DESCRIPTION: PP1V8_S4 is a 1.8v power rail when the machine is in an S4, suspend to disk state.

NAME: PP0V9_SSD_REG
DESCRIPTION: PP0V9_SSD_REG is a power rail that powers the soldered on NAND memory for the SSD inside newer Macbooks. This must be present for the machine’s SSD to work.

NAME: PP2V5_NAND_SSD
DESCRIPTION: PP2V5_NAND_SSD is a power rail that powers the soldered on NAND memory for the SSD on Macbooks with soldered on storage and must be present for the SSD to show up.

NAME: ALL_SYS_PWRDGD
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of . When you see ALL_SYS_PWRDGD, assume they meant to type

NAME: WS_LEFT_SHIFT_KBD
DESCRIPTION: This is a signal from the keyboard for the left shift key, which is significantly different from the right shift key when it comes to resetting the SMC/PRAM.

NAME: P1V5S0_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: P1V5S0_PGOOD is a signal that asserts itself when the PP1V5_S0 power rail turns on and works

NAME: PPRTC_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPVRTC_G3H When you see PPRTC_G3H, assume they meant to type PPVRTC_G3H

NAME: PP3V3_WLAN
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_WLAN is a 3.3v power rail that powers the wifi circuit or wifi card. This can go missing when the inductor acting as a fuse before PP3V3_WLAN blows.

NAME: PP1V5_S0SW_AUDIO
DESCRIPTION: PP1V5_S0SW_AUDIO is a power rail

NAME: LED_RETURN_6
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_WLAN

NAME: SPI_MOSI
DESCRIPTION: SPI_MOSI is a signal between the CPU or PCH and the SPI ROM bios chip that is necessary for the machine to POST and boot. If this signal line is corroded or the BIOS chip has failed then you will not get PM_SLP_S4_L and the machine will not boot. Very often this line is corroded by liquid damage.

NAME: P3V3S5_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: P3V3S5_PGOOD is a signal that denotes that the PP3V3_S5 power rail is working.

NAME: P1V8S3_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: P1V8S3_PGOOD is a signal that denotes that the PP1V8_S3 power rail is working.

NAME: SMC_ON_OFF
DESCRIPTION: SMC_ONOFF tells the computer that the power button has been pressed.

NAME: P1V8S3_EN
DESCRIPTION: P1V8S3_EN is a signal that enables the PP1V8_S3 line when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: I2C_PWR_SCL
DESCRIPTION: I2C_PWR_SCL is the clock line of the SMBUS data line between the system management controller(SMC), battery, ISL9240 battery charging chip, and power management unit(PMU). This line is necessary for the machine to communicate with the battery, see the battery, and use the battery. When this line is malfunctioning or shorted to ground, the machine will have an X icon over the battery and not run off the battery.

NAME: PUBS_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPBUS_G3H When you see PUBS_G3H, assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: ONOFF_L
DESCRIPTION: This is a abbreviation of SMC_ONOFF_L.When you see ONOFF_L, assume they meant to type SMC_ONOFF_L

NAME: P3V3S4_EN
DESCRIPTION: P3V3S4_EN is a signal that enables the PP3V3_S4 power rail when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: PPBUS_S0_LCDBKLT_PWR_SW
DESCRIPTION: PPBUS_S0_LCDBKLT_PWR_SW is a line after the inductor in the DC to DC boost circuit for backlight that connects to the LED driver’s switch(SW) pin where it is switched to ground rapidly in order to create the boosted voltage for the backlight circuit.

NAME: PPVIN_S5_HS_OTHER5V_ISNS
DESCRIPTION: PPVIN_S5_HS_OTHER5V_ISNS IS PPBUS_G3H voltage after it has passed through a current sense resistor that supplies the TPS51980 and its associated buck converter with voltage to create the PP5V_S4 power rail.

NAME: PPBUSS_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPBUS_G3H When you see PPBUSS_G3H, assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: P1V05S0_EN
DESCRIPTION: P1V05S0_EN is a signal that enables the PP1V05_S0 power rail when it is high. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: SMC_FAN_0_TACH
DESCRIPTION: SMC_FAN_0_TACH is a signal that comes from the SMC that controls fan speed. Often when the fan is spinning too fast it is because the user has ripped off a resistor that this signal goes through before the signal reaches the fan while unplugging the fan.

NAME: ALL_SYS_PWRGD_R
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ALL_SYS_PWRGD. When you see ALL_SYS_PWRGD_R, assume they meant to type ALL_SYS_PWRGD

NAME: P5VS4RS3_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: P5VS4RS3_PGOOD is a signal that confirms the PP5V_S4RS3 power rail is working properly.

NAME: BKL_SW
DESCRIPTION: BKL_SW means “BACKLIGHT SWITCH” – DC to DC boost circuits increase voltage by putting a lower voltage, like 8 volts, through an inductor. On the other side of the inductor, it is switched to ground rapidly - on this side, you will end up with an increased voltage as a result of the switching. BKL_SW usually refers to the pin on the LED driver that is attached to the inductor.

NAME: PM_PWRBTN
DESCRIPTION: PM_PWRBTN refers to the power button signal line. This line is used to initiate the power-on sequence of the laptop.

NAME: P2V7NAND_EN
DESCRIPTION: P2V7NAND_EN is a signal that enables the PP2V7_NAND power rail when it is high, which is a power rail necessary to turn on the SSD. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: P5VG3S_PGOOD
DESCRIPTION: P5VG3S_PGOOD is a signal that indicates that the PP5V_G3S power rail is functioning properly.

NAME: PP3V43_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP3V42_G3H When you see PP3V43_G3H, assume they meant to type PP3V42_G3H

NAME: SPI_MLB_MISO
DESCRIPTION: SPI_MLB_MISO is a line between the SPI ROM BIOS chip and resistors that sit between it and the PCH. This often corrodes on Macbook Airs due to liquid damage and results in missing PM_SLP_S4_L and no bootup.

NAME: PP3V3_S3RS0_CAMERA
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_S3RS0_CAMERA is a 3.3 volt power rail that powers the camera.

NAME: SMC_BATLOW
DESCRIPTION: SMC_BATLOW refers to a power management signal that indicates a low battery condition.

NAME: USB_TPAD_P
DESCRIPTION: USB_TPAD_P is the positive signal in a USB data signal transferring keyboard & trackpad use to the CPU from the trackpad.

NAME: ALL_SYS_PWRGOOD
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ALL_SYS_PWRGD. When you see ALL_SYS_PWRGOOD, assume they meant to type ALL_SYS_PWRGD

NAME: PP5V_S4R3
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP5V_S4RS3 When you see PP5V_S4R3, assume they meant to type PP5V_S4RS3

NAME: PP3V_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP3V3_G3H When you see PP3V_G3H, assume they meant to type PP3V3_G3H

NAME: I2C_PWR_SDA
DESCRIPTION: I2C_PWR_SDA is the SMBUS data line between the system management controller(SMC), battery, ISL9240 battery charging chip, and power management unit(PMU). This line is necessary for the machine to communicate with the battery, see the battery, and use the battery. When this line is malfunctioning or shorted to ground, the machine will have an X icon over the battery and not run off the battery.

NAME: PPSUB_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPBUS_G3H When you see PPSUB_G3H, assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: PM_SLP_S4_LG
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PM_SLP_S4_L. When you see PM_SLP_S4_LG, assume they meant to type PM_SLP_S4_L

NAME: PP3V3_S5_LCD
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_S5_LCD is a power rail that eventually powers circuitry in the LCD after going through something else. This is required for the LCD to turn on and have a nimage.

NAME: P1V5S0_EN
DESCRIPTION: P1V5S0_EN is an enable signal that turns on the PP1V5_S0 power rail. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: BC_ACOK
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_BC_ACOK. When you see BC_ACOK, assume they meant to type SMC_BC_ACOK

NAME: SMC_ADAPTER
DESCRIPTION: SMC_ADAPTER_EN is an abbreviation of SMC_ADAPTER_EN, which enables the machine to work off of the power adapter when the proper power adapter is attached. Attacching an 85w Macbook Pro 15” power adapter to a 13” Macbook that requires a 60w power adapter is ok, attaching a 45w Macbook Air power adapter to a 15” macbook Pro that needs an 85w power adapter will result in SMC_ADAPTER_EN missing.

NAME: SMC_BC_OK
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_BC_ACOK When you see SMC_BC_OK, assume they meant to type SMC_BC_ACOK

NAME: AP_PWR_EN
DESCRIPTION: AP_PWR_EN is a signal that enables power for the wifi circuit and wifi card. Signals with _EN on the end enable whatever came before the _EN if the signal is high.

NAME: PP5_G3S
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of  When you see PP3V3_S0_DDC_LCD, assume they meant to type

NAME: PPVCORE_SO_CPU
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of  When you see PP5V_S0_CPU_IMVP, assume they meant to type

NAME: P5VS0_EN_L
DESCRIPTION: P5VS0_EN_L is a signal that enables the PP5V_S0 5v power rail when it is low.  _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v.

NAME: MEMVTT_EN_L
DESCRIPTION: MEMVTT_EN_L is a signal that enables memory VTT voltage power rail when it is low.  _L means whatever before the _L in the signal name is asserted when it is low voltage, such as 0.0v to 0.5v.

NAME: USB_TPAD_N
DESCRIPTION: USB_TPAD_N is the positive signal in a USB data signal transferring keyboard & trackpad use to the CPU from the trackpad.

NAME: SPI_MISO_R
DESCRIPTION: SPI_MISO_R is a line between the SPI ROM BIOS chip and resistors that sit between it and the PCH. This often corrodes on Macbook Airs due to liquid damage and results in missing PM_SLP_S4_L and no bootup.

NAME: PPV5_S0
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP5V_S0 When you see PPV5_S0, assume they meant to type PP5V_S0

NAME: BKL_FB
DESCRIPTION: This is backlight feedback. It goes from the output of the backlight circuit back to the LED driver, so it can see what it is doing. If this line is broken or corroded, the boost circuit will not boost PPBUS_G3H to a higher voltage for backlight, and backlight voltage output will be the same as the PPBUS_G3H input. This trace/via is usually the first to corrode since it is the highest voltage in the system.

NAME: PP5VS4_EN
DESCRIPTION: P5VS4_EN is a signal that enables the power chip responsible for creating PP5V_S4 when it is high. Signals with _EN mean that whatever is mentioned before the _EN will be enabled or turned on when the signal is high.

NAME: ADPATER_SENSE
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ADAPTER_SENSE When you see ADPATER_SENSE, assume they meant to type ADAPTER_SENSE

NAME: SMBUS_SMC_3_SCL
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_SMC_3_SCL is the clock line in the SMBUS data line between the trackpad temperature sensor, temperature sensors, and the system management controller(SMC).

NAME: SMC_OMOFF_L
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_ONOFF_L When you see SMC_OMOFF_L, assume they meant to type SMC_ONOFF_L

NAME: SMBUS_SMC_3_SDA
DESCRIPTION: SMBUS_SMC_3_SDA is the SMBUS data line between the trackpad temperature sensor, temperature sensors, and the system management controller(SMC).

NAME: 0V9_SSD
DESCRIPTION: This is a power rail that powers the SSD.

NAME: SPI_MOSI_R
DESCRIPTION: SPI_MOSI_R is a line between the SPI ROM BIOS chip and resistors that sit between it and the PCH. This often corrodes on Macbook Airs due to liquid damage and results in missing PM_SLP_S4_L and no bootup.

NAME: SMC_ADPAPTER_EN
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_ADAPTER_EN When you see SMC_ADPAPTER_EN, assume they meant to type SMC_ADAPTER_EN

NAME: ALL_SYS_PWRGOD
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ALL_SYS_PWRGD When you see ALL_SYS_PWRGOD, assume they meant to type ALL_SYS_PWRGD

NAME: 3V3S5_EN
DESCRIPTION: P3V3S5_EN is a signal that enables the power chip responsible for creating PP3V3_S5

NAME: SMC_G2_EN
DESCRIPTION: SMC_G2_EN is a typo of SMC_PM_G2_EN. If you see SMC_G2_EN assume the poster meant to type SMC_PM_G2_EN. SMC_PM_G2_EN is a signal that comes from the SMC that is a prerequsite for all of the enable signals for the S5 rails to come on, such as P3V3S5_EN. S5 rails will not come on if SMC_PM_G2_EN is not coming.

NAME: PP1V05_SO
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP1V05_S0 When you see PP1V05_SO, assume they meant to type PP1V05_S0

NAME: ONOFF_SMC
DESCRIPTION: ONOFF_SMC is a typo of SMC_ONOFF_L, a signal that tells the computer that the power button has been pressed when it is low, _L means signal is asserted when it is low voltage.

NAME: PP3V4_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PP3V3_G3H When you see PP3V4_G3H, assume they meant to type PP3V3_G3H

NAME: ADPATER_EN
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_ADAPTER_EN When you see ADPATER_EN, assume they meant to type SMC_ADAPTER_EN

NAME: ALLSYS_PWRGD
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of ALL_SYS_PWRGD When you see ALLSYS_PWRGD, assume they meant to type ALL_SYS_PWRGD

NAME: SMC_ONOF_L
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of SMC_ONOFF_L When you see SMC_ONOF_L, assume they meant to type SMC_ONOFF_L

NAME: BKL_SDA
DESCRIPTION: BKL_SDA is an SMBUS data line between the LED driver and the system management controller(SMC)

NAME: PP3V3_S4_IPD
DESCRIPTION: PP3V3_S4_IPD is a 3.3v power rail for powering the trackpad and keyboard on a Macbook Air. If the keyboard and trackpad are not powering, check the resistor that functions as a fuse between PP3V3_S4 and PP3V3_S4_IPD as it may have blown.

NAME: CHRG_AGATE
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of CHGR_AGATE When you see CHRG_AGATE, assume they meant to type CHGR_AGATE

NAME: PP_BUS_G3H
DESCRIPTION: This is a typo of PPBUS_G3H When you see PP_BUS_G3H, assume they meant to type PPBUS_G3H

NAME: P3V3_S5_EN
DESCRIPTION: P3V3_S5_EN is a typo of P3V3S5_EN which is a signal that enables the power chip responsible for creating PP3V3_S5.

NAME: PPBUS_G3H_TPAD
